# Pandora Box - Tech Stack & Preferences

## Stack
- Next.js 15.5.5 (App Router, Turbopack)
- React 19, TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS 4
- PostgreSQL (Supabase) + Supabase Auth
- React Hook Form + Zod validation
- React Query (client data), useState/Context (local state)
- Jest + React Testing Library

## Code Style
- Functional components with arrow functions
- Named exports preferred
- TypeScript: explicit types, avoid `any`
- Files: PascalCase for components, camelCase for utils/actions
- Single component per file
- Brief comment above functions/sections, none inside function bodies

## Structure
src/
├── app/ # Next.js pages
├── components/ # Shared components
│ └── ui/ # Base UI components
├── features/ # Feature modules
│ └── [feature]/
│ ├── components/
│ ├── actions/ # Server actions
│ └── schemas/ # Zod schemas
├── lib/ # Utils, Supabase config
└── hooks/ # Custom hooks

## Server Actions
- Use `"use server"`, validate with Zod
- Return: `{ success: boolean; data?: T; error?: string }`
- Place in feature-based `actions/` folders

## Key Patterns
- Server Components by default, `"use client"` only when needed
- React Query for client-side fetching
- Tailwind utilities (avoid @apply)
- Mobile-first responsive design
- Co-locate tests with source files